          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2JPNKTO"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The Kyoto University Research Reactor (KUR)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The graphite thermal column (TC-Pn) in KUR. The",
                "nominal neutron flux intensity of TC-Pn is 5.86E+10",
                " (n/cm2/sec) at 1 MW power operation. The AUTHORs",
                "have confirmed that the TC-Pn was extremely",
                "thermalized on the basis of Westcott's convention in",
                "another experiment. (See Fig. 8 in the REL-REF.)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Np-237 standardized solution (Np(NO3)4 in 4 M HNO3)",
                "was used for samples. Impurities of the solution were",
                "measured with an alpha-ray spectroscopy and a mass",
                "spectrometer.",
                "           -Np-237 : Am-241 = 1 : 0.0014.",
                "           -Am-243, Cm-244 and the other Np isotopes",
                "            were not observed.",
                "Two standardized solutions equivalent to about 950 and",
                "370 Bq were dropped onto pieces of glass filters.",
                "The filters were dried by an infrared ramp.",
                "The activity of the sample were determined using the",
                "312-keV gamma-ray emitted from Pa-233.",
                "The deduced activities were:",
                "           Sample1: 961 +- 22 Bq and",
                "           Sample2: 379 +- 9 Bq.",
                "The samples and the monitors were irradiated in",
                "the TC-Pn for 30 minutes under 1-MW power operation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Based on Westcott's convention method.",
                "Because the neutron flux in the TC-Pn is well",
                "thermalized, epithermal component in Westcott's",
                "convention method was negligibly small."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High purity germanium detector, relative",
                "efficiency of 25%. The gamma-ray peak efficiencies of",
                "the Ge detector were measured using a mixed source",
                "AM-8140 (Eckert & Ziegler Nuclitec GmbH, Germany) :",
                "Am-241, Cd-109, Co-57, Ce-139, Hg-203, Sn-113, Cs-137,",
                "Co-60 and Y-88 whose uncertainty of source-activity",
                "was 1.5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction rates of the Np-237 samples were",
                "obtained from the yield of the 984.45-keV gamma rays",
                "emitted from the irradiated samples.",
                "The thermal-neutron fluxes were derived using the",
                "reaction rates and the thermal cross sections of the",
                "monitors (Sc-45, Co-59, Mo-98, Ta-181 and Au-197).",
                "Thermal capture cross sections and g-factors of",
                "the monitors were taken from the REL-REF.",
                "The cross section of Np-237 was derived from",
                "the reaction rates and the activities of the samples,",
                "and the deduced thermal-neutron flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-shielding coefficients for the monitors were",
                "calculated from neutron capture cross-sections and",
                "area densities of the monitors.",
                "Those for the Np-237 samples were estimated to be",
                "unity from its number of nuclei."
              ]
            }
          ],
